# Testing discipline

Do **not** add tests by default. More tests here have been harmful than helpful when they only assert classNames, testids, or thin UI wiring.

Before writing any test, read `docs/agents/testing.md`. Only add a test when it clears that keep bar (user asked / agreed seam, duplicated truth that can drift, or non-obvious pure logic with an independent expected value).

If unsure, skip the test.
